/* Parent hub page. It has no body of its own: with Type="xmenu", Unraid's
 * PageBuilder gathers every child page whose Menu equals this page's basename
 * ("UnraidRsync") and renders them as tabs (ordered by the ":rank" suffix).
 *
 * MENU PLACEMENT DECISION (Unraid 7.x):
 *   We use Menu="OtherSettings", NOT Menu="Settings".
 *   In the webGui, "Settings" is itself a top-level page (Settings.page,
 *   Menu="Tasks:4"); the section hubs shown UNDER it are pages like
 *   OtherSettings.page ("System Settings", Menu="Settings:1") and
 *   UserPreferences.page (Menu="Settings:3"). Plugins attach to one of those
 *   section hubs. Setting Menu="Settings" would make this hub a sibling of the
 *   Settings tab on the menu bar instead of nesting it under Settings.
 *   Pointing at OtherSettings places "Unraid Rsync" inside the System Settings
 *   section, matching how shipping plugins (recycle.bin -> Utilities,
 *   ca.cleanup.appdata) and dynamix's own settings pages declare themselves.
 *   The .plg's launch="Settings/UnraidRsync" (<TopMenu>/<HubBasename>) keeps
 *   the plugin's deep-link working with this placement.
 *   Verified against unraid/webgui PageBuilder.php find_pages() and
 *   DefaultPageLayout.php xmenu child-gathering.
 */
?>
